casebody.data:
No. 11,

Original.

United States v. Louisiana. Solicitor General Rankin for the United States. Joseph V. Ferguson, II for the Anderson-Prichard Oil Corporation, movant.

The motion by the Solicitor General to dismiss as moot the motion by Anderson-Prichard Oil Corporation for extraordinary relief and for amendment or interpretation of the decree of this Court is granted. The motion by Anderson-Prichard Oil Corporation for extraordinary relief and for amendment or interpretation of the decree of this Court is dismissed.

The Chief Justice took no part in the consideration or decision of these motions.

(For decree, see 351 U. S. 978.)
